# TinyFish Web Agent — Vigil Integration Rules

**Source of truth:** [TinyFish Web Agent Documentation](https://docs.tinyfish.ai)

Reference the official docs before writing any TinyFish integration code. TinyFish code lives under **`src/server/`** (see [nextjs-api-backend-rules.mdc](.cursor/rules/nextjs-api-backend-rules.mdc)).

- [Endpoints](https://docs.tinyfish.ai/key-concepts/endpoints) — `/run`, `/run-async`, `/run-sse`
- [Runs](https://docs.tinyfish.ai/key-concepts/runs) — lifecycle, statuses, polling, cancel
- [Authentication](https://docs.tinyfish.ai/authentication) — `X-API-Key` header
- [API Reference (SSE)](https://docs.tinyfish.ai/api-reference/automation/run-browser-automation-with-sse-streaming)
- [Error Codes](https://docs.tinyfish.ai/error-codes) — MISSING_API_KEY, INVALID_API_KEY, FORBIDDEN (credits), etc.

---

## CORE PRINCIPLES

- Write concise, production-grade TinyFish integrations.
- Always generate structured JSON schemas in goals.
- Use explicit numbered steps for multi-step workflows.
- Include error-handling instructions inside every goal.
- Default to predictable, strict output formats.
- Avoid vague instructions like "get the data".
- Include fallback behavior when elements are missing.
- Keep schema identical across all batch runs — no dynamic keys.
- Always specify expected return structure.
- Validate TinyFish resultJson before trusting — treat as unknown.

---

## API CONFIGURATION

```
Base URL:     https://agent.tinyfish.ai/v1/automation/
Auth Header:  X-API-Key: YOUR_TINYFISH_API_KEY
Content-Type: application/json
Env Variable: TINYFISH_API_KEY
```

### CRITICAL NAMING — snake_case only

- Field is `browser_profile` — NEVER `browserProfile`
- Field is `proxy_config` — NEVER `proxyConfig`

### Authentication

- ALWAYS use `X-API-Key` header
- NEVER use `Authorization: Bearer` — TinyFish does not use Bearer tokens
- NEVER access `process.env.TINYFISH_API_KEY` directly
- ALWAYS import from `config/env.ts` with Zod validation

```typescript
// config/env.ts — add to existing Zod schema
TINYFISH_API_KEY: z.string().min(1);
```

### Request Body Shape

All three endpoints accept the same body. Required: `url`, `goal`. Optional: `browser_profile`, `proxy_config`, `api_integration`, `feature_flags`.

```typescript
interface TinyFishRequest {
  url: string; // Required. Target website URL.
  goal: string; // Required. Natural language description of the task.
  browser_profile?: "lite" | "stealth"; // Optional. Default: 'lite'
  proxy_config?: {
    enabled: boolean;
    country_code?: string; // e.g. 'US' | 'GB' | 'CA' | 'DE' | 'FR' | 'JP' | 'AU' (IN if supported)
  };
  api_integration?: string; // Optional. e.g. "vigil" — for analytics.
  feature_flags?: { enable_agent_memory?: boolean }; // Optional.
}
```

### Browser Profiles

- `lite` — default, fast. Use for: company blogs, changelogs, Product Hunt, GitHub, most startup marketing pages.
- `stealth` — anti-bot environments. Use for: BSE/NSE portals, LinkedIn Jobs, G2, Capterra, competitor pricing pages.

```typescript
// Vigil profile reference
const BROWSER_PROFILES = {
  bseCirculars: "stealth",
  nseCirculars: "stealth",
  competitorPricing: "stealth",
  competitorJobsLinkedIn: "stealth",
  competitorJobsSite: "lite",
  g2Reviews: "stealth",
  competitorBlog: "lite",
  productHunt: "lite",
  githubReleases: "lite",
} as const;
```

