## EXECUTION MODES

Three modes exist. Choose based on the user interaction pattern. See [Endpoints](https://docs.tinyfish.ai/key-concepts/endpoints).

### 1. run-sse — Streaming (Primary for Vigil)

```
POST https://agent.tinyfish.ai/v1/automation/run-sse
```

Use when:

- User triggers a manual scan from the dashboard
- You need real-time progress streamed to the UI
- Building the ScanProgress live feed component

Expect (SSE event types):

- `STARTED` — includes `runId`
- `STREAMING_URL` — optional; URL to watch browser live (valid 24h)
- `PROGRESS` — browser actions (e.g. `purpose`)
- `HEARTBEAT` — keep-alive
- `COMPLETE` — includes `status` (`COMPLETED` | `FAILED` | `CANCELLED`), `resultJson`, and optionally `error` / `help_message`

```typescript
const response = await fetch(
  "https://agent.tinyfish.ai/v1/automation/run-sse",
  {
    method: "POST",
    headers: {
      "X-API-Key": env.TINYFISH_API_KEY,
      "Content-Type": "application/json",
    },
    body: JSON.stringify({
      url: "https://competitor.com/pricing",
      goal: pricingGoal,
      browser_profile: "stealth",
      proxy_config: { enabled: false },
    }),
  },
);
// response.body is a ReadableStream — pass to parseSSEStream()
```

### 2. run — Synchronous / Blocking (Quick Checks)

Official docs use `/run` (not `run-sync`). See [Endpoints](https://docs.tinyfish.ai/key-concepts/endpoints).

```
POST https://agent.tinyfish.ai/v1/automation/run
```

Use when:

- Task is short and fast (under ~30 seconds)
- You need immediate response without streaming
- Simple compliance spot-checks

Runs created via `/run` cannot be cancelled. The request blocks until completion.

```typescript
const response = await fetch(
  "https://agent.tinyfish.ai/v1/automation/run",
  {
    method: "POST",
    headers: {
      "X-API-Key": env.TINYFISH_API_KEY,
      "Content-Type": "application/json",
    },
    body: JSON.stringify({
      url: "https://bseindia.com/corporates/Notices_Circulars.html",
      goal: complianceGoal,
      browser_profile: "stealth",
      proxy_config: { enabled: false },
    }),
  },
);
const run = await response.json();
// run.result contains extracted data when run.status === "COMPLETED"
```

### 3. run-async — Background Jobs (Automation Mode)

```
POST https://agent.tinyfish.ai/v1/automation/run-async
```

Use when:

- User has enabled automation (scheduled scans)
- Large scraping workflows — 10+ pages
- Background jobs that must not block the request

Returns `{ run_id: string }` — MUST store and poll for completion. See [Runs](https://docs.tinyfish.ai/key-concepts/runs).

**Run statuses:** `PENDING` | `RUNNING` | `COMPLETED` | `FAILED` | `CANCELLED`

**Poll for result:** `GET https://agent.tinyfish.ai/v1/runs/{run_id}` — response has `status`, `result` (when COMPLETED), `error` (when FAILED).

**Cancel run:** `POST https://agent.tinyfish.ai/v1/runs/{run_id}/cancel` — only for runs created via `/run-async` or `/run-sse`.

```typescript
// Step 1 — Start async job
const response = await fetch(
  "https://agent.tinyfish.ai/v1/automation/run-async",
  {
    method: "POST",
    headers: {
      "X-API-Key": env.TINYFISH_API_KEY,
      "Content-Type": "application/json",
    },
    body: JSON.stringify({
      url: pageUrl,
      goal: pageGoal,
      browser_profile: "stealth",
      proxy_config: { enabled: false },
    }),
  },
);
const { run_id } = await response.json();

// Step 2 — Store run_id in ScanRun document
await scanRepository.updateExternalRunId({ scanRunId, run_id });

// Step 3 — Poll GET /v1/runs/{run_id} until status is COMPLETED or FAILED
// Use async-poller.ts for polling logic. Run object: run_id, status, result, error, streamingUrl
```

