## ARCHITECTURE — WHERE TINYFISH LIVES IN VIGIL

```
src/
├── server/
│   ├── lib/
│   │   └── tinyfish/
│   │       ├── client.ts           # ONLY file that calls fetch to TinyFish API
│   │       ├── sse-parser.ts       # Parses SSE ReadableStream → TinyFishSSEResult
│   │       ├── async-poller.ts     # Polls run-async status until completion
│   │       ├── tinyfish.types.ts   # All TinyFish types — no any, no unknown
│   │       └── goals/
│   │           ├── pricing.goal.ts
│   │           ├── jobs.goal.ts
│   │           ├── reviews.goal.ts
│   │           ├── changelog.goal.ts
│   │           ├── features.goal.ts
│   │           └── compliance.goal.ts
│   ├── services/
│   │   ├── scan.service.ts         # Orchestrates TinyFish via client
│   │   └── change-detection.service.ts
│   └── repositories/
│       └── scan.repository.ts      # All DB queries for ScanRun, Change, Competitor
```

### Architecture Rules

- `server/lib/tinyfish/client.ts` is the ONLY file that calls `fetch` to TinyFish — no exceptions
- Services call the client — NEVER call fetch directly in services
- Route handlers call services — NEVER import from `server/lib/tinyfish` in route handlers (import from `@/server/services/...` instead)
- Goals live in `server/lib/tinyfish/goals/` — one file per page type
- Goals are exported as builder functions, NOT string constants (allows parameterisation)
- All types in `tinyfish.types.ts` — NEVER use `any`
- Validate `resultJson` shape with Zod before use — treat as `unknown` until confirmed

