## PARALLEL SCANNING — VIGIL CORE PATTERN

ALWAYS use `Promise.allSettled` for parallel page scans.
NEVER use `Promise.all` — one page failure must never block other pages.

```typescript
// services/scan.service.ts

const pageResults = await Promise.allSettled(
  pages.map((page) =>
    tinyfishClient.runSSE({
      url: page.url,
      goal: resolveGoal(page.type),
      browser_profile: page.browserProfile ?? "stealth",
      proxy_config: { enabled: false },
    }),
  ),
);

const resolved = pageResults.map((result, i) => ({
  page: pages[i],
  success: result.status === "fulfilled" && result.value.success,
  data: result.status === "fulfilled" ? result.value.resultJson : null,
  error: result.status === "rejected" ? String(result.reason) : null,
}));

// Determine ScanRun status
const allFailed = resolved.every((r) => !r.success);
const someFailed = resolved.some((r) => !r.success);
const status = allFailed ? "failed" : someFailed ? "partial" : "completed";
```

### ScanRun Status Rules

| Condition           | Status      | triggeredBy            |
| ------------------- | ----------- | ---------------------- |
| All pages succeeded | `completed` | `user` or `automation` |
| Some pages failed   | `partial`   | `user` or `automation` |
| All pages failed    | `failed`    | `user` or `automation` |
| Currently running   | `running`   | `user` or `automation` |

### Manual-First Rule — CRITICAL

- `triggeredBy` MUST be `'user'` for all dashboard-triggered scans
- `triggeredBy` is `'automation'` ONLY when user has explicitly enabled automation in Settings
- NEVER auto-trigger a TinyFish run without explicit user action or enabled automation setting

